On 5/27/10 1&#58;33 AM, Yang, Wei wrote&#58;
Hi Sarah,

I have seen this issue from time to time with 2010... xrootd releases,

and adding a trailing / will likely work around the problem.  In your
case, can you do

/path/xrd iut2-dc1.iu.edu&#58;1094 locateall /xrdfs

without the trailing /, it should list all your data servers. If you have to add a trailing slash

to the above command, than we will need to look at the configuration.

regards,
Wei Yang  |  yangw@....  |  650-926-3338(O)

On May 26, 2010, at 5&#58;25 PM, Sarah Williams wrote&#58;

Hi all,

I&#39;ve found a behavior in configure_xrootdfs that I don&#39;t think was
intended. I&#39;m working with XrootdFS 3.0rc4.  My command was&#58;
$VDT_LOCATION/vdt/setup/configure_xrootdfs &#92;
--user xrootd &#92;
--cache /xrdfs &#92;
--xrdr-host iut2-dc1.iu.edu &#92;
--xrdr-storage-path /xrdfs

When I started xrootdfs, it did not mount correctly.  The output of ls
-l looked like&#58;
drwxr-xr-x  15 root root  4096 Mar 11 13&#58;55 usr
drwxr-xr-x  19 root root  4096 Mar 11 20&#58;44 var
?---------   ? ?    ?        ?            ? xrdfs

I struggled with this for awhile, and finally looked back at my notes
from last year.  I took that command, which is&#58;

$VDT_LOCATION/vdt/setup/configure_xrootdfs &#92;
--user xrootd &#92;
--cache /xrdfs/ &#92;
--xrdr-host iut2-dc1.iu.edu &#92;
--xrdr-storage-path /xrdfs/

That command worked.  Is it intended that cache and xrdr-storage-path
require trailing slashes? If so, could we get that added to the
documentation?

I apologize in advance for reporting and running.  I will be out
tomorrow through Monday.  If you need any further info, the other
members of MWT2 can probably get it for you.  The install is in
iut2-grid8&#58;/opt/bestman-gateway/.

--Sarah

- -- Sarah Williams
